<paragraph blockId="38.[192,1441,217,533]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,217,241]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus without close relatives, but not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[1092,1369,217,242]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1092,1191,217,241]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Psoralis</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1386,1440,218,242]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[286,666,250,274]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabaeus">
<emphasis box="[286,490,250,274]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Psoralis sabaeus</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
, which is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Weeks, 1901" authorityName="Weeks" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idee">
<emphasis box="[1168,1345,250,274]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Pamphila idee</emphasis>
Weeks, 1901
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[276,407,282,307]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Fig. 11â€“12</figureCitation>
). Keys to J. 
<quantity box="[541,630,282,307]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.11506" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" unit="in" value="43.9">43.9 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[637,801,282,306]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphologically, distinguished from its relatives by a very conspicuous, large gray stigma and nearly unmarked dark brown hindwing ventral (sometimes with small pale dots). Male genitalia distinctive, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Nicolay" box="[820,989,347,371]" firstAuthor="Nicolay" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref27965" refString="Nicolay, S. S. 1980. Descriptions of new Hesperiidae from Panama and Ecuador (Pyrginae and Hes- periinae). Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 59: 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1980">Nicolay (1980</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7): uncus broad, not narrowing in the middle, tegumen with a pair of long dorsal processes directed caudad, gnathos the same length and width as uncus, prominent in lateral view, penis stout caudad with elongated phallobase, valva nearly oval, twice as long and wide with shirt harpe pointed dorsad, closely approaching ampulla (
<bibRefCitation author="Nicolay" box="[1268,1428,445,469]" firstAuthor="Nicolay" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref27965" refString="Nicolay, S. S. 1980. Descriptions of new Hesperiidae from Panama and Ecuador (Pyrginae and Hes- periinae). Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 59: 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1980">Nicolay 1980</bibRefCitation>
). In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly25.7.1:A134C, aly 
<date box="[1223,1348,477,501]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" value="2532-12-02">2532.12.2</date>
:A142C, aly594.9.1:G589A, aly423.4.2:C199G, aly25.7.1:A226G.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[192,1440,558,615]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,558,582]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, denoting the second half of [Pso] 
<emphasis box="[192,256,590,614]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Ralis</emphasis>
, the genus where these species were placed previously.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[192,1088,638,663]" box="[192,1088,638,663]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,638,662]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[493,546,639,663]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nicolay, 1980" authorityName="Nicolay" authorityYear="1980" box="[701,1085,638,663]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Psoralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concolor">
<emphasis box="[701,907,638,662]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Psoralis concolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nicolay" box="[915,1085,639,663]" firstAuthor="Nicolay" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref27965" refString="Nicolay, S. S. 1980. Descriptions of new Hesperiidae from Panama and Ecuador (Pyrginae and Hes- periinae). Bulletin of the Allyn Museum 59: 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1980">Nicolay, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[192,823,687,712]" box="[192,823,687,712]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,687,711]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Moncina A. 
